<p>Build a layout card without touching JSON. Pick a template to start, drop in components, then copy the result into the <code>stack_layout_card_spec</code> field of your managed configuration. <a href="/projects/managed-info/support/customising-managed-info/">Learn more about layout cards.</a></p>

<details style="margin:14px 0 18px;border:1px solid var(--light);border-radius:8px;padding:8px 14px;background:var(--subtle-bg)">
  <summary style="cursor:pointer;font-weight:600;font-size:14px;color:var(--text)">How to apply this card to a device (MANAGED INFO 1.2.0.0 or later)</summary>
  <div style="font-size:13px;line-height:1.55;padding:10px 0 4px">
    <p style="margin:0 0 8px">Layout cards are delivered through your EMM as a managed configuration string against the MANAGED INFO app. Devices need MANAGED INFO version <strong>1.2.0.0</strong> or later for the <code>stack_layout_card_spec</code> field to be honoured.</p>
    <ol style="margin:0 0 8px;padding-left:20px">
      <li>Build your card in the editor above and click <strong>Copy</strong> in the JSON panel to grab the minified spec.</li>
      <li>In your EMM (Android Management API console, Intune, Workspace ONE, SOTI, Knox, etc.) open the managed configuration for the MANAGED INFO app.</li>
      <li>Find the <code>stack_layout_card_spec</code> string field. Paste the JSON in as a single line.</li>
      <li>Save and push the policy. On the next sync the device will replace its current card with the new layout. No app restart required.</li>
    </ol>
    <p style="margin:0 0 6px"><strong>Tips:</strong></p>
    <ul style="margin:0 0 0;padding-left:20px">
      <li>Keep the spec under 20,000 characters. The editor's counter goes amber from 10,000 and red above 20,000, where some EMMs start truncating string values.</li>
      <li>Image URLs must be HTTPS and reachable from the device. Self-hosted images need to be on a host the device can resolve.</li>
      <li>If a device doesn't pick up the change, confirm it's on 1.2.0.0 or later (Settings, Apps, MANAGED INFO, version) and force a managed config sync from your EMM.</li>
      <li>To go back to the default card, push an empty string for <code>stack_layout_card_spec</code>.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</details>

